race.comment: TASSIE POWER (2) spiked his numbers beaten a whisker stepping up to this distance at Hobart. He will be fitter again and arrives here on a 4-day return. Positions on-speed and must be pleasing. Has scope for more improvement and will be hard to beat. ARIANNA'S GOLD (3) has missed a whisker at the track both starts this preparation and raced a 3.40F the latest over 1200m. Looks suited first attempt at the trip and rates to be right in the finish. SEDITIOUS AWARD (8) peaks on a quick back-up from the TASSIE POWER race. She improved again beaten 2.5L in that contest and draws an inside barrier this evening. Has to be considered. LADY BE COOL (7) was beaten less than 2L here before the spell and needed the first-up outing behind Henley Extreme. In good hands and maps for a soft run. Quick improvement is likely.
